The 2 celts are very similar – in shape, flake scars, condition (white patina, lightly rolled; 327 has more iron-staining on one face than 328, where staining is almost absent: neither have significant staining on second face) & raw material (grey patches in flint). Although no clue is given in the register, it seems likely that the celts were buried together.
